{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C and grease a large baking dish or tray.","Slice courgettes in half lengthways. With a small sharp knife, make an incision 5 mm around the edge then diagonally score and scoop out the flesh and reserve. Place courgette shells in prepared baking dish.","Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place bread and mint in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>Turbo\/2 sec\/2 times<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 4.5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add reserved courgette flesh, olives, salt and pepper, chop <nobr>1 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr> then cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool.","Place eggs, 60 g reserved Parmesan and ricotta in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add 50 g reserved breadcrumbs and cooled courgette mixture then mix <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Stir with spatula then mix again <nobr>5 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Fill courgette shells with mixture.","Combine remaining breadcrumbs with remaining grated Parmesan then sprinkle over filled courgettes. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes (200°C), removing foil 5 minutes before the end of cooking time.","Remove from oven and leave to rest for a few minutes before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 courgettes, large","90 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","60 g bread, torn in pieces","15 g fresh mint leaves","120 g red onions, quartered","30 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","12 green olives, pitted","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","2 medium eggs","80 g ricotta cheese"]}],"id":"r239602","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-c8XODCRXrcE\/XZVRMq0nfqI\/AAAAAAAAdLM\/njHp712Z0pYdKWENpggDFyJ_mPN1CTv_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hlzjkBc7-ce98OWZ.png","title":"Stuffed Courgettes - Zucchine farcite","publishedAt":"2018-05-28T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"23.5 g","fat":"24 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"13.5 g","calories":"1585 kJ \/ 380 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking dish, sharp knife, aluminium foil, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Courgettes, from the French word <i>courge<\/i>, meaning 'squash', are a summer squash that is harvested before it is fully grown. For this recipe, the insides have been hollowed out before being stuffed with familiar Italian ingredients: creamy ricotta, fresh mint and salty olives. Topped with breadcrumbs and baked in the oven, these stuffed courgettes are a deliciously light and flavoursome main.","To make this recipe suitable for vegetarians, substitute the Parmesan cheese for a vegetarian hard cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","4 portions"]}